data.chText: 爬；爬行；匍匐行进
data.enText: to move forward on your hands and knees, with your body close to the ground

data.chText: 我们的宝宝刚开始会爬。
data.enText: Our baby is just starting to crawl.

data.chText: 一个男人正从燃烧着的残骸往外爬。
data.enText: A man was crawling away from the burning wreckage.

data.chText: （昆虫）爬行
data.enText: when an insect crawls , it moves forward on its legs

data.chText: 有只蜘蛛正顺着你的腿往上爬。
data.enText: There's a spider crawling up your leg.

data.chText: 缓慢行进
data.enText: to move forward very slowly

data.chText: 来往车辆缓缓而行。
data.enText: The traffic was crawling along.

data.chText: 几个星期慢慢地过去了。
data.enText: The weeks crawled by.

data.chText: 卑躬屈膝；谄媚；巴结；拍马屁
data.enText: to be too friendly or helpful to sb in authority, in a way that is not sincere, especially in order to get an advantage from them

data.chText: 她对老板总是谄媚奉承。
data.enText: She's always crawling to the boss.
make your skin crawl

data.chText: 使人毛骨悚然；让人起鸡皮疙瘩
data.enText: to make you feel afraid or full of disgust
come/crawl out of the woodwork

data.chText: 突然露面；纷纷出笼
data.enText: if you say that sb comes/crawls out of the woodwork , you mean that they have suddenly appeared in order to express an opinion or to take advantage of a situation

data.chText: 他博彩中奖后，八杆子打不着的亲戚都突然来登门造访。
data.enText: When he won the lottery, all sorts of distant relatives came out of the woodwork.
be crawling with sth

data.chText: 挤满；爬满
data.enText: to be full of or completely covered with people, insects or animals, in a way that is unpleasant

data.chText: 这地方挤满了记者。
data.enText: The place was crawling with journalists.

data.chText: 她的头发上爬满了虱子。
data.enText: Her hair was crawling with lice.

data.chText: 缓慢的速度
data.enText: a very slow speed

data.chText: 来往的车辆放缓速度慢慢前行。
data.enText: The traffic slowed to a crawl.

data.chText: 爬泳；自由泳
data.enText: a fast swimming stroke that you do lying on your front moving one arm over your head, and then the other, while kicking with your feet

data.chText: 游自由泳的运动员
data.enText: a swimmer doing the crawl

tr: a slow mode of locomotion on hands and knees or dragging the body
example: a crawl was all that the injured man could manage
the traffic moved at a creep
the traffic advanced at a crawl

tr: arms are moved alternately overhead accompanied by a flutter kick
in the case of people or animals with the body near the ground
example: The crocodile was crawling along the riverbed

tr: they often don't know how to crawl"
example: European children learn the breast strok
The old cheese was crawling with maggots

tr: feel as if crawling with insects

value.def: When you crawl, you move forward on your hands and knees.

example.ex: Don't worry if your baby seems a little reluctant to crawl or walk...
example.tran: 如果你的宝宝不爱爬也不爱走，不要担心。

example.ex: I began to crawl on my hands and knees towards the door...
example.tran: 我开始手脚并用朝门口爬去。

example.ex: As he tried to crawl away, he was hit in the shoulder.
example.tran: 他试图爬走时肩膀中枪了。

value.def: When an insect crawls somewhere, it moves there quite slowly.

example.ex: I watched the moth crawl up the outside of the lampshade.
example.tran: 我看着飞蛾爬到灯罩外面。

value.def: If someone or something crawls somewhere, they move or progress slowly or with great difficulty.

example.ex: I crawled out of bed at nine-thirty...
example.tran: 我9点半才勉强从床上爬起来。

example.ex: They had not foreseen the higher inflation in France when most of Western Europe was crawling out of recession...
example.tran: 当西欧的大多数国家正从经济衰退中缓慢复苏时，他们并没有预见到法国的通货膨胀率会升高。

example.ex: Hairpin turns force the car to crawl at 10 miles an hour in some places.
example.tran: 在一些地段，U形弯路使得汽车只能以每小时10英里的速度缓慢行进。

example.ex: The traffic on the approach road slowed to a crawl.

value.def: If you say that a place is crawling with people or animals, you are emphasizing that it is full of them.

example.ex: This place is crawling with police.
...rock-hard earth littered with rubbish and crawling with vermin.
example.tran: 丢满垃圾、爬满虫子的坚硬土地

value.def: The crawl is a kind of swimming stroke which you do lying on your front, swinging one arm over your head, and then the other arm.
If something makes your skin crawl or makes your flesh crawl, it makes you feel shocked or disgusted.

example.ex: I hated this man, his very touch made my skin crawl.
example.tran: 我讨厌这个男人，他碰我一下我都觉得恶心。

trans: 使人反感;使毛骨悚然;使心惊肉跳
